{
  "texts": [
    "Emerging technologies such as edge intelligence have gained traction in the application of AI closer to the network edge in support of B5G needs.",
    "Edge intelligence is an alternative AI application that can be effectively employed in the monitoring of crops enabling a more efficient and sustainable food supply.",
    "Edge intelligence represents the convergence of AI and edge computing.",
    "Currently, a pivotal and widely employed methodology in this domain involves model compression, with a particular focus on techniques such as parameter pruning and quantization.",
    "The resources often used for edge intelligence include Central Processing Units (CPUs), Graphics Processing Units (GPUs), and Field Programmable Gate Arrays (FPGAs) (Liu et al., 2021)."
  ]
}